{{Unreferenced|date=July 2010}} '''Blackwater, New Mexico''' is the designation of a [[HVDC]] back-to-back facility for the power exchange between the asynchronous power grids of Texas and New Mexico. It was built by Brown Boveri in 1985 and can transfer a power up to 200 megawatts. The used voltage is 57 kV.
