'''Elin Lerum Boasson''' (born 28 May 1978) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[environmentalism|environmentalist]] and was chairman of [[Natur og Ungdom]] in 2001 and 2002.<ref>[https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=no&u=http://www.uis.no/conferences/international_conference_on_energy_and_sustainability/article14697-4998.html&ei=iuFdS4n3K5ab8Qa85ujzBA&sa=X&oi=translate&ct=result&resnum=6&ved=0CB4Q7gEwBQ&prev=/search%3Fq%3D%2522Elin%2BLerum%2BBoasson%26hl%3Den%26rlz%3D1R2SNYI_enUS342 Elin Lerum Boasson] at [[University of Stavanger]], translated to English, access date January 2010.</ref> She became active in the organisation in 1991, and joined the board in 1997 before she was elected deputy chairman in 1999.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nrk.no/nyheter/norge/1.519603 |language=Norwegian |title=Jentekupp i Natur og Ungdom |publisher=NRK |date=7 January 2001 |accessdate=11 October 2013}}</ref> She has a Master of Political Science degree from the [[University of Oslo]] and has since 2005 worked at [[Nansen Institute]] as a [[researcher]] (as of 2009).<ref>[https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=no&u=http://www.fni.no/cv/cv-elb.html&ei=iuFdS4n3K5ab8Qa85ujzBA&sa=X&oi=translate&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CAkQ7gEwAA&prev=/search%3Fq%3D%2522Elin%2BLerum%2BBoasson%26hl%3Den%26rlz%3D1R2SNYI_enUS342 Elin Lerum Boasson] at [[Fridtjof Nansen Institute]], translated to English, access date January 2010.</ref>

