The {{nihongo|'''Seto Windhill'''|瀬戸ウインドヒル発電所|Seto uindo hiru hatsudensho}} is a collection of [[wind turbine]]s located on the peaks of mountains along the [[Sadamisaki Peninsula]], in the town of [[Ikata, Ehime|Ikata]], [[Ehime Prefecture]], [[Japan]].  The windfarm borders the Seto Wind Hill Park.

The installation consists of 11 [[Mitsubishi Heavy Industries]] MWT-1000s with a [[Intermittent power source#Terminology|nameplate capacity]] of 1000 [[kilowatt|kW]].<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title = Mitsubishi to construct 11 MW wind farm in Ehime| work = WindPower Monthly| publisher = Haymarket Media Group Ltd.| date = 1 July 2002| url = http://www.windpowermonthly.com/article/962351/mitsubishi-construct-11-mw-wind-farm-ehime| format = | doi = | accessdate = 11 October 2014 }}</ref> They were erected starting September 2002, and began full operation in October 2003.

